The paper focuses on using convolutional neural networks for phoneme sequence recognition, which is a task commonly studied in the field of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of convolutional neural networks also involves image processing techniques (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning techniques, which falls under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves the use of signal processing techniques, which falls under the sub-category of digital signal processing (cs.SD).
